rest_of_day_open: I feel like the rest of my week is going to go well. My plans are to relax for the days leading up to Thursday; on Thursday, I'm leaving for the beach for the weekend. I am really looking forward to resting and relaxing by the pool and eating seafood.
critical_positive: I think what worked well about the conversation was that my conversation partner was able to come up with many questions to keep the conversation going and open-ended. He was able to converse with me about several popular culture topics to keep the flow of the conversation going. This worked well.
critical_negative: I think a lot of the awkwardness of our conversation stemmed from the glitch in the middle of the conversation that prevented us from seeing each others screen. It also stemmed from the awkward silences that interspersed the conversation we were having. Kirk is a jovial man, so he did not make it super awkward.

rest_of_day_open: Busy. with a dental cleaning and medication pick up 40 miles away on Thursday Reorganizing and trying to set up a move to a cheaper place to live by the end of this month. I see more frustration with the way things are going within my life and in this country as a hole.
critical_positive:
It felt odd to meet someone socially on a video chat. Gestures were not fully recognized by me. 

Had one technical glitch when I lost the feed briefly, but could still hear each other.

Hard to talk with someone when you are not in full view of each other. 

Hard for one person to be the one who attempts to be engaging.
critical_negative:
Jim was sort of shy and did not seem to want to engage or appeared reluctant to start a conversation. He would have appeared more engaging if he was not in a reclined position during the entire conversation. 

It made it appear as if he did not want to put forth any effort towards being engaging.
